  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Preoperative radiotherapy and pelvic surgery is recommended to many patients with rectal
      cancer.For women there are theoretical reasons to believe that the treatment may affect
      hormone levels, sexual function and wellbeing. To address these questions a longitudinal
      observational study was initiated where patients, before preoperative radiotherapy and one
      year after surgery, take blood tests and answer two questionnaires.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
